710761f-a.text: Twelfth Avenue, east side, at West 38th Street, showing the northerly corner of the New York Central Railroad yards at this location. The photographer is viewing northeastward towards Eleventh Avenue and 39th Street. At the left is the shed used for the calling of live stock unloaded from the river barges. March 17, 1929. P. L. Sperr.

712523f-a.text: 38th Street, north side, east of Twelfth Avenue; the view is northeast. March 17, 1929. P. L. Sperr.

710759f-a.text: Twelfth Avenue, west side, at foot of 38th Street, showing work on new midtown tunnel which will link Manhattan with Weehawken, New Jersey. August 30, 1934. P. L. Sperr.

710760f-b.text: Twelfth Avenue, east side, at West 38th Street, showing the New York Central Railroad yards at this location. In the center of these, on the west side of Eleventh Avenue, is the distinctive ventilator building of the Lincoln Tunnel under the North (Hudson) River. The vague online of the Empire State Building appears in the background. The photographer is viewing eastward. October 20, 1939. P. L. Sperr.
